<i>Posted by Nulian on 03-15-2001 03:11 PM:</i>

<p><b> Misinformation</b></p>

<p>Tantolar, <br />
<br />
Please refrain from posting information which is false.<br />
<br />
True: Gleed will not give you the quest or respond to quest keywords if you are not amiable or better - you get the 'we don't trust you enough yet' message.<br />
<br />
False: You can't complete the quest until you are amiable.<br />
<br />
I just got my bow, and here's how:<br />
<br />
Once I had the tail, I killed dwarves until my faction with both storm and frost giants was dubious. I was still dubious to dwarves at this point, so now I can walk through most of Kael and all of Thurgadin without a problem.<br />
<br />
Go to Kael, get behind Gleed, sneak. Check he's indifferent. <br />
<br />
Hand in the tail, and get my shiny new bow.<br />
<br />
Now I just need to spend some time slaughtering giants to make the dwarves like me again.<br />
<br />
So to re-iterate, even though Gleed won't <b>tell</b> you about the quest when you're indifferent, he <b>will</b> give you the reward when you hand in the tail.<FONT face="arial, helvetica" size="2"><br>
__________________<br>
<b>Nulian Greenhand</b><br />
