<i>Posted by Braslo on 04-05-2001 04:23 PM:</i>

<p><b> </b></p>

<p>The ressing part will work, both directions, but the cleric will not be able to drag the corpse around.  Kael is one of the places that has that new no-drag-my-enemy code.  Since the giants in that arch can see the cleric, they'd kill him.<br />
<br />
A workaround might be to duel someone at the zoneline (or suicide on one of the giants near there), then leave that corpse while you do the suicide run through the arch.  Then the cleric resses the arch corpse, do quest, then stand and wait for the zoneline res.  (remember, you can get revived several times on a single corpse)<br />
<br />
Another option to get OUT after you've done the quest part is to use a thurgadin potion, that way you don't have to die again.  If you can stand there after getting a res, you should be able to stand there to cast a spell to.  (also, a druid/wizard port or translocate can be used, but now you're starting to form a group effort, lol)<FONT face="arial, helvetica" size="2"><br>
