<i>Posted by Evenshadow on 05-02-2001 12:18 AM:</i>

<p><b> Moving Giants....</b></p>

<p>Hi all.   Just thought I would post a way for those of us without a large guild, or a non-KOS Cleric or mage friend to move some giants out of the way to get to Gleed.  <br />
<br />
     Ages ago, a couple friends and I made a bunch of little Rallos Zek worshipping ogres, and had a druid bring em to Kael. We primarily used em for scouting purposes, but occasionally they are nice for corpse pulling too.<br />
<br />
    It occured to me that a small ogre with a long range bow and SoW could make a hell of a train of see invis giants.   The bow (I recommend oak: 125 rng) should be as long a range as possible, to give your mini ogre a head start.  <br />
<br />
    Have a friend make one, give him a bow and arrows, sow him at the WL entrance, and have him go into the passage towards Gleed's area.  You may have to make an ogre of your own to show him EXACTLY what it is you want done.  Find a friend who is tactically competent, or you will get very frustrated before you are done<img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt=""> <br />
<br />
   Once you get to where the three giants are, guarding Gleeds area, instruct him to shoot the farthest back Guard (the single one).  Once again, range is key here. He needs as much of a head start as possible, so use the bow at its maximum range.  The guard farthest towards Gleed, once he has been potted by your mini ogre, will charge your friend:  He has to run like hell.    As the guard goes past the 2 that are side by side, he will agro them as well, and you have a nice train.<br />
<br />
   After instructing my friend, I switched back to my ranger and waited invis far back from the passage entrance.   We decided to run the train down towards the WL entrance, giving me enough room to slip in behind em and go get my bow.<br />
<br />
   Once at Gleed, follow the excellent instructions given above to get your new bow, then use a thurgadin gate potion to get out, or do it all again to get out.  Thurg potion is a hell of a lot safer<img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt=""><br />
<br />
   This is not theoretical:  My Kael faction is about as bad as it can possibly be and I got my bow quite a while ago, first try.<br />
<br />
   A Word of Warning:   your sacrificial ogre will get quite a few giants on his tail - DO NOT TRAIN PEOPLE.<br />
Do this when the zone is quiet, make a hotkey and use it a lot , and have your lil ogre stop a ways before the zone, so some poor fool who just zoned in doesnt have a bunch of see ivis giants dumped on him.  <br />
<br />
     Safety here is paramount:   I can't justify getting a new bow at the cost of someone elses life ( an innocent bystander).   Please be careful, the nature of this trick makes it dangerous.<br />
<br />
    Good luck with your new bows<img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt=""><br />
<br />
                               Evenshadow</p>
<hr>
<i>Posted by Neathon on 05-02-2001 01:08 AM:</i>

<p><b> Kill Giants!</b></p>

<p>Kill 3 Giants that see invis 2 guard the archway that will have to be done together or FD pulled.<br />
<br />
The 3rd is at the far end of the Archway. <br />
<br />
Then FD pull Gleed so you get Him or his Dog single. You can do them at the same time it just hurts a lot more.<br />
<br />
I did this with a single group twice. Both times on the first attempt we wiped out. <br />
<br />
The second attempt both times we succesfully killed Gleed and his dog one time one by one, the other time both at once. <br />
<br />
A single 55+ group that knows what they are doing can do this easily. <br />
<br />
Gleed or his PH is a 1 or 2 hour spawn time. I've only seen his PH twice. He has dropped the bow all 3 times we have killed him.<FONT face="arial, helvetica" size="2"><br>
__________________<br>
Neathon Silverthought<br />
<i>Shining Path</i><br />
