<i>Posted by Ubergoober on 05-04-2001 12:18 PM:</i>

<p><b><img src="images/icons/icon14.gif" alt="Thumbs up" width="15" height="15" border="0"> Just did it!</b></p>

<p>Well, I have been hanging around ICEWALL and Great Divide killing dwarfs to get their heads to improve Kael faction. After two days and about 20 heads I get to high aimiable. I was just about ready to head to Kael to turn in more heads when I hit track and Vluudeen was up! I got a 54 mage and druid together quickly and headed to southern entrance to the wurm caves. <br />
<br />
Vluudeen is in a nook almost right inside the tunnel, so is fairly easy to pull single. Once we had him outside cave and in a clear area we had mage pet and myself (using swarmcaller) tank. Vluudeen hit for close to 130, but we managed to kill him without having to summon a second pet. I think I was healed by druid using chloroblast about 3-4 times during the fight.<br />
<br />
Turning in the tail to Gleed was very easy, as in the process of waiting for Vluudeen to spawn I had gotten to high aimiable with Storm and Frost Giants. I also got a nice faction jump to kindly from doing the quest.<br />
<br />
As to the bow itself, it is awesome! The thing is ready to fire by the time the first shot has hit, practically! This bow reaffirms my belief that rangers should go with Kael faction.<FONT face="arial, helvetica" size="2"><br>
