<i>Posted by Ternak on 06-22-2001 05:43 PM:</i>

<p><b> Vluudeen</b></p>

<p>Finally killed this sucker last night after cmping for him on many nights previous.<br />
<br />
Someone was doing tenth ring quest apparently, and Giants had cleared the entire GD zone just before I logged in.   Suspecting that Vluudeen might pop, I notified my Guild that I might need reinforcements.<br />
<br />
Sure enough when giants despawned, Vluudeen poped just inside the southern most tunnel off the main one through wurm cave.  Pulled him single easily and kited him around for 10-15 minutes till the cavalry arrived.  I put a lot of arrows into him while weaving around between shardwurms south of the cave, but I could barely see damage.  In addition to having a ton of hit points, out of melee range, his regen rate can keep up with a lot of crits.<br />
<br />
With 52 Shammie, 51 Cleric, 53 Druid, and two late 40s arriving, Vluudeeen went down pretty easy.  We had enough mana left to pull Shardtooth just a few minutes later.<br />
<br />
On my way to turn in tail this evening <img src="images/smilies/biggrin.gif" border="0" alt=""> <br />
<br />
Great guide here, so many thanks.  Just need to have giants clear the zone more often so Vluudeen will pop for us.<FONT face="arial, helvetica" size="2"><br>
