<i>Posted by Tarmor on 08-09-2001 07:32 PM:</i>

<p><b> </b></p>

<p>With both Gleed and this buddies around him no longer seeing invisible, this is much easier to accomplish for those of us who are not exactly on good terms with the giants.  HOWEVER, be careful the position you have to stand in to give the bow to Gleed is just (and I do mean just) outside of the agro range of one of the guard giants.  Additionally when you drop your camo make sure that your sneak is on and holding otherwise Gleed will agro on you too (you would swear he has eyes in the back of his head)<br />
<br />
You're best way out (if you were like me and ended up dropping sneak after the trade....) is to gate out using a Thurg potion.  Gleed does path up the little ramp to come get you, but this gives you just enough time to drink the potion.<br />
<br />
In retrospect you have to wonder....if some little ranger con'd you out of your prized bow, wouldn't you get a bit miff'd.<FONT face="arial, helvetica" size="2"><br>
__________________<br>
Tarmor out of Surefall<br />
